1
00:00:02,310 --> 00:00:05,810
Cinderella
Takamine Takane

2
00:00:06,170 --> 00:00:11,070
Well, I'd like to decide on 
the other main role, the prince.

3
00:00:12,930 --> 00:00:15,910
I think I will be a candidate as well then.

4
00:00:18,150 --> 00:00:21,240
I knew he had his sights set on her.

5
00:00:22,980 --> 00:00:24,870
I will be a candidate as well!

6
00:00:25,910 --> 00:00:27,080
Who is he, even?

7
00:00:27,080 --> 00:00:28,340
Oh?

8
00:00:35,890 --> 00:00:39,180
I would like to open a vote for the role, then.

9
00:00:39,640 --> 00:00:42,140
Please submit your votes anonymously.

10
00:00:44,390 --> 00:00:45,640
Cast for the Cinderella play

11
00:00:44,390 --> 00:00:45,640
Cinderella
Takamine Takane

12
00:00:44,390 --> 00:00:45,640
Prince

13
00:00:44,390 --> 00:00:45,640
Shirota Koushi 
(1 vote)

14
00:00:44,390 --> 00:00:45,640
Ouji Seiya
 (26 votes)

15
00:00:45,640 --> 00:00:47,900
<i>Nooo!</i>

16
00:00:50,270 --> 00:00:52,010
I'm so sorry...

17
00:00:52,010 --> 00:00:53,930
I couldn't get the role.

18
00:00:55,480 --> 00:00:57,950
<i>I knew she was going to be mad...</i>

19
00:00:58,950 --> 00:01:03,000
Um, so that thing about 
making Ouji your closet...

20
00:01:04,070 --> 00:01:04,960
What?

21
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:07,680
That was a joke, of course.

22
00:01:07,680 --> 00:01:12,520
My aim was to get you inspired 
to try to get the Prince role.

23
00:01:12,520 --> 00:01:12,920
Huh?

24
00:01:13,310 --> 00:01:18,780
After you lost the vote, you applied 
for the role of Prince's Guard.

25
00:01:15,090 --> 00:01:19,140
Stage Visitor C
Shindou Nobuchika

26
00:01:15,090 --> 00:01:19,140
Guard of the Prince
 Shirota Koushi

27
00:01:20,030 --> 00:01:21,300
Why's that?

28
00:01:21,300 --> 00:01:22,600
Well...

29
00:01:23,310 --> 00:01:24,960
If I'm the Prince's guard,

30
00:01:24,960 --> 00:01:27,920
I figure I'll get roughly 
the same amount of time as him,

31
00:01:27,920 --> 00:01:32,330
so then you won't need to ask Ouji 
for help because I can be there for you.

32
00:01:36,180 --> 00:01:39,450
<i>Wait, she foresaw all of this?!</i>

33
00:01:39,870 --> 00:01:43,790
Besides, it wouldn't be any good if you
 hid away behind the scenes again

34
00:01:43,790 --> 00:01:46,550
and I had to see your gloomy face.

35
00:01:46,970 --> 00:01:49,400
If you try something new,

36
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:51,910
you might be able to enjoy things more openly.

37
00:01:54,010 --> 00:01:55,370
Speaking of...

38
00:01:55,370 --> 00:01:56,510
What is it?

39
00:01:56,510 --> 00:02:02,030
If all you wanted was for me 
to try to get the role of the prince,

40
00:02:02,030 --> 00:02:04,700
then I wonder who voted for me?

41
00:02:05,460 --> 00:02:06,570
Who knows.

42
00:02:09,190 --> 00:02:11,110
Someone must have unusual preferences.

43
00:02:33,170 --> 00:02:41,180
<i></i><i>Please Put 
Them On,
 Takamine-san</i>

44
00:03:41,990 --> 00:03:46,990
I'll Let You Do a Dry Run

45
00:03:42,870 --> 00:03:46,010
I'll let you do a dry run.

46
00:03:48,900 --> 00:03:51,980
<i>In order to make our Cinderella play 
that we're putting on</i>

47
00:03:51,980 --> 00:03:54,080
<i>for the cultural festival a success,</i>

48
00:03:54,460 --> 00:03:58,300
<i>we used the time after class 
and our homeroom time to prepare.</i>

49
00:03:58,300 --> 00:04:02,650
<i>And now, we're just one day away 
from the big event.</i>

50
00:03:58,300 --> 00:04:03,550
<i></i><i>Cinderella</i>

51
00:04:04,430 --> 00:04:06,500
Tomorrow is the big day!

52
00:04:06,500 --> 00:04:10,520
Anyone who's not busy, please go 
support the groups that need help.

53
00:04:10,820 --> 00:04:14,050
Let's all work together 
to get this over the finish line!

54
00:04:14,050 --> 00:04:15,520
I'm sorry, President.

55
00:04:15,850 --> 00:04:18,770
If you've got a minute, could you please 
help us with the stage backdrops?

56
00:04:18,770 --> 00:04:20,570
Of course.

57
00:04:20,570 --> 00:04:24,490
If there's anyone else free, 
could you please come and help too?

58
00:04:24,490 --> 00:04:26,300
I'll come help.

59
00:04:26,300 --> 00:04:28,580
I'm almost done here, so I'll come help too!

60
00:04:28,580 --> 00:04:29,480
I'll—

61
00:04:30,020 --> 00:04:31,480
Oh, sorry!

62
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:32,970
It's fine.

63
00:04:32,970 --> 00:04:35,580
<i>I guess they won't need my help.</i>

64
00:04:36,740 --> 00:04:37,670
Shirota-kun.

65
00:04:38,420 --> 00:04:40,810
You're free as well, arent you?

66
00:04:40,810 --> 00:04:42,130
Could you please give us a hand?

67
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:44,520
It's the backdrop with the stairs.

68
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:46,320
I need you to add a light.

69
00:04:46,320 --> 00:04:48,110
There's already one on the left side,

70
00:04:48,110 --> 00:04:51,070
so you can use that as reference 
to add it on the right.

71
00:04:51,070 --> 00:04:52,100
S-Sure.

72
00:04:54,610 --> 00:04:58,750
Hey, did the President just touch that Shirota guy?

73
00:04:58,750 --> 00:05:00,850
Why someone as forgettable as him?

74
00:05:00,850 --> 00:05:03,330
It's because President is like a goddess.

75
00:05:03,330 --> 00:05:07,620
I bet she just spoke to him because 
he's so lonely and isolated and pathetic.

76
00:05:07,620 --> 00:05:09,160
<i>The pressure is intense...</i>

77
00:05:10,070 --> 00:05:11,390
<i>But, now that I think about it,</i>

78
00:05:11,390 --> 00:05:15,760
<i>she never used to interact
 with me in front of others.</i>

79
00:05:16,300 --> 00:05:17,620
<i>Is there some sort of reason?</i>

80
00:05:19,010 --> 00:05:20,420
Is something wrong?

81
00:05:20,420 --> 00:05:21,590
N-No...

82
00:05:21,590 --> 00:05:23,070
Hey, Shirai!

83
00:05:23,070 --> 00:05:25,820
You made the left and right 
lights exactly the same!

84
00:05:25,820 --> 00:05:26,510
Huh?

85
00:05:26,940 --> 00:05:29,260
Oh! I'm sorry! I'll fix it right away!

86
00:05:29,260 --> 00:05:32,260
We don't have time. Just leave it.

87
00:05:32,690 --> 00:05:33,720
Youch.

88
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:34,980
Now he's done it.

89
00:05:41,930 --> 00:05:43,760
Eternal Virgin Road.

90
00:06:23,490 --> 00:06:26,650
<i>We're back to before I started 
working on the backdrop?</i>

91
00:06:26,650 --> 00:06:28,050
<i>Why?</i>

92
00:06:28,050 --> 00:06:28,860
Shirota-kun.

93
00:06:29,850 --> 00:06:30,810
Over here.

94
00:06:30,810 --> 00:06:31,980
C-Coming.

95
00:06:32,780 --> 00:06:36,830
<i>Wait, did she do this to undo my mistake?</i>

96
00:06:39,200 --> 00:06:43,360
Those stairs are for the important 
scene where I drop my slipper.

97
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:45,480
You better make it perfect.

98
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:47,050
<i>Yeah, go figure.</i>

99
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:49,470
If you've got it, hurry up.

100
00:06:49,470 --> 00:06:50,460
Right...

101
00:06:51,820 --> 00:06:53,300
President?

102
00:06:53,300 --> 00:06:55,180
Huh? President?

103
00:06:56,530 --> 00:06:57,600
What's up?

104
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:59,090
Oh, there you are!

105
00:06:59,090 --> 00:07:01,470
We kind of need help with the backdrops...

106
00:07:01,470 --> 00:07:03,560
But what are you doing there?

107
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:07,920
Oh, I was just checking behind the sets 
to make sure everything's good.

108
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:09,030
I see.

109
00:07:09,030 --> 00:07:11,170
Do you need help with something?

110
00:07:11,170 --> 00:07:11,970
Yeah.

111
00:07:11,970 --> 00:07:13,240
Once you're done there,

112
00:07:13,530 --> 00:07:17,490
do you think you could
help with the backdrops?

113
00:07:17,490 --> 00:07:21,370
<i>How can she remain 
so calm in a situation like this?!</i>

114
00:07:22,020 --> 00:07:24,860
Sure, I'm done here. I can help.

115
00:07:30,410 --> 00:07:34,470
If anyone else is free, 
could you please come and help too?

116
00:07:34,470 --> 00:07:36,290
I'll come help.

117
00:07:36,290 --> 00:07:38,600
I'm almost done here, so I'll come help too!

118
00:07:42,420 --> 00:07:43,850
Here you go.

119
00:07:43,850 --> 00:07:45,690
Thanks, President!

120
00:07:45,690 --> 00:07:46,980
Be careful.

121
00:07:48,390 --> 00:07:49,490
Shirota-kun.

122
00:07:49,490 --> 00:07:51,050
You're free as well, aren't you?

123
00:07:51,050 --> 00:07:52,510
Could you please give us a hand?

124
00:07:52,510 --> 00:07:53,750
S-Sure...

125
00:07:54,890 --> 00:07:57,070
Um, I'm sorry.

126
00:07:57,070 --> 00:07:59,250
The panties are not fully on...

127
00:07:59,250 --> 00:08:00,570
I know.

128
00:08:00,570 --> 00:08:02,210
Did you think I wouldn't notice?

129
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:04,120
I already took care of it.

130
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:05,920
Wait, when?!

131
00:08:06,340 --> 00:08:09,130
When I caught that piece of wood,

132
00:08:09,130 --> 00:08:12,110
I spread my legs and engaged 
the gluteus maximus, gluteus medius,

133
00:08:12,110 --> 00:08:15,790
the femoral muscle, and the tensor tympani
 muscle to shift it into position.

134
00:08:15,790 --> 00:08:17,140
<i>That's amazing.</i>

135
00:08:17,550 --> 00:08:21,020
Do it quicker from now on
so this won't happen again.

136
00:08:21,020 --> 00:08:23,640
Slowta-kun—no, slowpoke.

137
00:08:23,640 --> 00:08:26,090
<i>That's not even a nickname anymore!</i>

138
00:08:26,090 --> 00:08:27,850
But anyway...

139
00:08:28,950 --> 00:08:31,070
let's continue with our preparations.

140
00:08:31,070 --> 00:08:33,280
R-Right...

141
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:02,770
Everyone, really good work today!

142
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:07,230
Let's get a lot of rest tonight and 
enjoy the cultural festival tomorrow!

143
00:09:07,230 --> 00:09:08,680
Good work!

144
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:13,720
<i>Wow, it's already so dark. 
I need to get home quick.</i>

145
00:09:14,900 --> 00:09:18,220
<i>Come to the Building A east rooftop entrance.</i>

146
00:09:14,900 --> 00:09:18,820
(President) Come to the Building A east rooftop entrance.

147
00:09:20,750 --> 00:09:24,000
<i>What does she me up here for?</i>

148
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:26,850
<i>I'm pretty sure the rooftop door is locked...</i>

149
00:09:26,850 --> 00:09:28,540
<i>Why bring me to this dead end?</i>

150
00:09:28,940 --> 00:09:31,520
<i>Did I do something to make her angry?</i>

151
00:09:31,910 --> 00:09:33,760
Oh, you were quick.

152
00:09:34,170 --> 00:09:35,470
I'm impressed.

153
00:09:36,010 --> 00:09:37,760
Why are you so jumpy?

154
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:39,880
Did you think I'd yell at you?

155
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:41,370
So you won't?

156
00:09:41,370 --> 00:09:42,620
Wait, what?

157
00:09:44,740 --> 00:09:46,820
Isn't it off limits?

158
00:09:46,820 --> 00:09:49,560
I went to the staff office to get permission.

159
00:09:49,560 --> 00:09:51,400
You are the student council president, I guess.

160
00:09:52,230 --> 00:09:54,790
Wow, there are so many stars.

161
00:09:55,230 --> 00:09:57,440
But why bring me here?

162
00:09:57,440 --> 00:10:01,450
I mean, looking at this night sky by myself
 would be kind of dull.

163
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:05,690
Also, the only reason 
that I invited you is

164
00:10:05,690 --> 00:10:08,570
that you were at the top of my LIME history.

165
00:10:08,570 --> 00:10:11,710
I'm sorry if you thought that 
there was more behind it.

166
00:10:11,710 --> 00:10:14,270
I'm quite all right with that...

167
00:10:14,810 --> 00:10:15,670
Besides...

168
00:10:16,190 --> 00:10:19,050
Staying at school this late...

169
00:10:19,050 --> 00:10:21,970
When I thought that 
this year might be the last time,

170
00:10:21,970 --> 00:10:23,390
I figured it would be a shame.

171
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:25,820
The last time?

172
00:10:25,820 --> 00:10:28,100
But there's another 
cultural festival next year.

173
00:10:28,510 --> 00:10:31,410
We're going to have 
entrance exams next year.

174
00:10:31,410 --> 00:10:33,790
Think about the mood 
the class will be in.

175
00:10:33,790 --> 00:10:39,000
Nobody is going to pick a large-scale 
project that will require us to stay late.

176
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,570
Oh, right.

177
00:10:41,490 --> 00:10:44,700
I like the evenings before events.

178
00:10:44,700 --> 00:10:47,770
The emotional high that 
you feel during the process,

179
00:10:47,770 --> 00:10:49,640
before something is about to begin.

180
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:50,780
On top of that,

181
00:10:50,780 --> 00:10:55,550
I had an easy-to-use closet at my disposal 
this year, so it was even more enjoyable.

182
00:10:55,950 --> 00:10:58,640
If I had known how convenient you'd be,

183
00:10:58,640 --> 00:11:02,260
I would have made you my closet 
for the cultural festival last year.

184
00:11:02,620 --> 00:11:04,500
I really missed out.

185
00:11:04,860 --> 00:11:06,430
Uh-huh...

186
00:11:08,180 --> 00:11:14,790
<i>Could it be that she invited me so that 
I could feel this emotional high as well?</i>

187
00:11:16,780 --> 00:11:20,650
Well, there's still the year after next.

188
00:11:22,290 --> 00:11:24,510
If you mean repeating 
a year, please do that alone.

189
00:11:24,510 --> 00:11:26,050
No, that's not it!

190
00:11:26,050 --> 00:11:27,740
I mean the cultural festival at university!

191
00:11:28,810 --> 00:11:33,090
I'm sure the cultural festival will be 
even bigger at the university.

192
00:11:33,090 --> 00:11:38,110
so we'll stay even later, 
maybe even spend the night to work.

193
00:11:38,110 --> 00:11:39,970
We'd have plenty of time to stargaze, too.

194
00:11:40,510 --> 00:11:47,100
Besides, I also intend to be by your side 
to support you at university.

195
00:11:50,470 --> 00:11:51,820
Stay the night?

196
00:11:51,820 --> 00:11:54,750
What kind of work are you thinking of?

197
00:11:54,750 --> 00:11:55,560
Pervert.

198
00:11:55,560 --> 00:11:59,280
Wha?! I-I-I wasn't thinking anything like that!

199
00:12:06,380 --> 00:12:08,490
<i>Why did it get so quiet?</i>

200
00:12:08,490 --> 00:12:09,610
<i>It's so awkward.</i>

201
00:12:09,610 --> 00:12:12,830
<i>I'm starting to feel like 
what I said was really embarrassing...</i>

202
00:12:13,480 --> 00:12:14,580
You know...

203
00:12:14,580 --> 00:12:15,210
Yes?!

204
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:19,290
Back when I read Cinderella for the first time,

205
00:12:19,290 --> 00:12:21,120
I felt repulsed by it.

206
00:12:21,570 --> 00:12:26,680
I mean, even though that girl wants 
something, she stays passive.

207
00:12:27,090 --> 00:12:30,730
If you want something, 
you ought to be proactive, shouldn't you?

208
00:12:30,730 --> 00:12:34,390
It's not like a fairy godmother 
will show up in real life.

209
00:12:35,610 --> 00:12:38,290
But to be honest, along with that repulsion,

210
00:12:38,290 --> 00:12:40,780
I also felt empathy.

211
00:12:40,780 --> 00:12:42,400
Not being able to muster the courage,

212
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:44,800
your pride getting in the way...

213
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:48,350
the more important things are, 
the harder it is to act...

214
00:12:48,350 --> 00:12:50,960
It makes you want to wait 
for something to come to you...

215
00:12:53,490 --> 00:12:54,640
But...

216
00:12:55,710 --> 00:12:57,180
I can say it now.

217
00:12:58,270 --> 00:12:59,270
In fact,

218
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:05,180
I think now is the only time I can say it.

219
00:13:22,350 --> 00:13:24,060
I-I...

220
00:13:24,730 --> 00:13:25,740
I am...

221
00:13:30,410 --> 00:13:32,260
I'm sorry, President.

222
00:13:32,260 --> 00:13:33,910
I didn't realize.

223
00:13:34,620 --> 00:13:37,550
You want to leave because it's cold!

224
00:13:38,460 --> 00:13:41,120
You should have just said something!

225
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:43,530
Your hands are so icy already.

226
00:13:43,930 --> 00:13:45,450
No, it's not—

227
00:13:47,060 --> 00:13:48,810
Please wear this on your way home.

228
00:13:48,810 --> 00:13:50,800
It would be terrible if you caught a cold.

229
00:13:55,180 --> 00:13:58,100
Sheesh, you should have noticed 
without me saying anything.

230
00:13:58,100 --> 00:13:59,180
Useless!

231
00:13:59,180 --> 00:14:01,180
I'm sorry...

232
00:14:01,940 --> 00:14:06,950
<i></i><i>Please Put Them On, 
Takamine-san</i>

233
00:14:06,950 --> 00:14:11,950
<i></i><i>Please Put Them On, 
Takamine-san</i>

234
00:14:11,950 --> 00:14:14,370
Haunted House 
Hall of the Spider

235
00:14:11,950 --> 00:14:14,370
Big Food
 Hall Festival

236
00:14:11,950 --> 00:14:14,370
<i></i><i>Fujihigashi Festival</i>

237
00:14:15,310 --> 00:14:20,050
We're going to hold a dress rehearsal prior 
to the performance before noon,

238
00:14:20,050 --> 00:14:23,130
so you're all free 
to enjoy yourselves until then.

239
00:14:23,130 --> 00:14:25,090
All right.

240
00:14:25,090 --> 00:14:28,520
Weird, where's Ouji? Is he late?

241
00:14:28,520 --> 00:14:30,800
Pretty ballsy for having a lead role.

242
00:14:31,210 --> 00:14:33,800
<i>Crap... I'm so freaking nervous!</i>

243
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:36,380
<i>I already have cold sweat 
running down my spine...</i>

244
00:14:36,380 --> 00:14:39,020
<i>And I only have two lines.</i>

245
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:43,760
Shirota-kun, do you have a minute?

246
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:45,070
Uh, sure.

247
00:14:46,540 --> 00:14:48,560
Um, President, where are we going?

248
00:14:48,560 --> 00:14:52,010
I couldn't leave you alone 
because you're so obviously nervous.

249
00:14:52,410 --> 00:14:55,540
Go enjoy some of the offerings to relax.

250
00:14:55,540 --> 00:14:57,000
I'll come along with you.

251
00:14:57,400 --> 00:15:00,210
<i>Oh, she's looking out for me?</i>

252
00:15:00,210 --> 00:15:02,740
I have the lead role in this play.

253
00:15:02,740 --> 00:15:05,470
Your role is so minor 
that it could be left out entirely,

254
00:15:05,470 --> 00:15:08,740
but I will not allow you to sully 
the play even the slightest bit.

255
00:15:08,740 --> 00:15:09,930
<i>That makes more sense...</i>

256
00:15:10,490 --> 00:15:11,890
<i>But...</i>

257
00:15:11,890 --> 00:15:14,460
Is the President holding that guy's hand?!

258
00:15:14,460 --> 00:15:16,030
Who the hell is he?!

259
00:15:16,030 --> 00:15:18,130
With that kind of useless loser?!

260
00:15:18,130 --> 00:15:21,140
<i>This situation is putting me 
under a different kind of pressure.</i>

261
00:15:21,140 --> 00:15:23,860
L-Let's go in here, then!

262
00:15:23,860 --> 00:15:25,980
Hall of the Spider

263
00:15:24,270 --> 00:15:25,060
Sure.

264
00:15:26,470 --> 00:15:28,800
<i>This is the Hall of the Spider.</i>

265
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:32,990
<i>All who enter shall be inflicted 
with the mysterious spider's curse.</i>

266
00:15:32,990 --> 00:15:37,850
<i>Should you wish to proceed regardless, 
you best steel your resolve first...</i>

267
00:15:38,610 --> 00:15:42,090
<i>We're not really exposed 
to the eyes of the public in here.</i>

268
00:15:42,090 --> 00:15:43,790
<i>And unless someone gets really close,</i>

269
00:15:43,790 --> 00:15:45,800
<i>they won't be able to identify us.</i>

270
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:49,940
<i>There shouldn't be any rumors of 
President walking around with a pathetic guy.</i>

271
00:15:49,940 --> 00:15:53,380
<i>It was a snap decision, 
but I really did quite well!</i>

272
00:15:53,380 --> 00:15:55,240
Should we get going then?

273
00:15:57,660 --> 00:16:01,310
<i>C-Could it be that President 
is afraid of this kind of stuff?!</i>

274
00:16:01,710 --> 00:16:04,010
<i>Now that I think about it, 
the thunder scared her, too.</i>

275
00:16:04,010 --> 00:16:06,100
<i>so I guess she's not good with jump scares...</i>

276
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:10,700
Um, if you're not good with this, 
we can turn back.

277
00:16:11,030 --> 00:16:12,960
What? Not good?

278
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:16,240
Are you suggesting that this 
fake kid stuff will scare me?

279
00:16:16,240 --> 00:16:17,740
Just so you know—

280
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:18,020
Be gone!

281
00:16:18,020 --> 00:16:20,200
You must not enter this place!

282
00:16:22,680 --> 00:16:24,990
<i>This is the Hall of the Spider.</i>

283
00:16:24,990 --> 00:16:29,210
<i>All who enter shall be inflicted 
with the mysterious spider's curse.</i>

284
00:16:29,210 --> 00:16:34,220
<i>Should you wish to proceed regardless, 
you best steel your resolve first...</i>

285
00:16:30,870 --> 00:16:34,220
Um, President, why don't we just leave?

286
00:16:34,610 --> 00:16:36,180
It's downward social comparison.

287
00:16:36,180 --> 00:16:37,170
Downward what?

288
00:16:37,170 --> 00:16:39,920
By comparing yourself to individuals 
you perceive as worse off,

289
00:16:39,920 --> 00:16:42,000
you can gain a boost in self-esteem.

290
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:47,330
In order to help you shake off your nerves, 
I over-exaggerated my shock for you.

291
00:16:47,330 --> 00:16:48,690
<i>R-Really now?</i>

292
00:16:49,610 --> 00:16:52,340
Come on, let's move towards the exit.

293
00:16:52,340 --> 00:16:53,750
R-Right...

294
00:16:57,350 --> 00:16:59,170
Please help meeeeee!

295
00:16:59,170 --> 00:17:00,340
Shirota-kun!

296
00:16:59,170 --> 00:17:02,380
The spiders are in my bodyyyy...

297
00:17:00,340 --> 00:17:01,330
Behind you!

298
00:17:01,330 --> 00:17:02,270
Spider! Spider!

299
00:17:02,270 --> 00:17:02,830
Wait!

300
00:17:05,230 --> 00:17:07,050
A-Are you all right, Shirota-kun?!

301
00:17:07,050 --> 00:17:08,990
What about the spider?! Did you get cursed?!

302
00:17:08,990 --> 00:17:10,400
It's fine, President!

303
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:11,250
Please calm down!

304
00:17:11,250 --> 00:17:14,700
Remember? This is a haunted house! 
It's not real!

305
00:17:16,460 --> 00:17:17,180
Huh?

306
00:17:18,110 --> 00:17:20,440
<i>This is the Hall of the Spider.</i>

307
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:24,780
<i>All who enter shall be inflicted 
with the mysterious spider's curse.</i>

308
00:17:24,780 --> 00:17:29,550
<i>Should you wish to proceed regardless, 
you best steel your resolve first...</i>

309
00:17:30,590 --> 00:17:32,050
Downward social comparison.

310
00:17:32,050 --> 00:17:34,290
Since you are slow on the uptake,

311
00:17:34,290 --> 00:17:35,810
I put on an act for you again.

312
00:17:35,810 --> 00:17:37,530
<i>That excuse is so sad!</i>

313
00:17:38,050 --> 00:17:45,120
<i>But she's really here toughing it out 
in this haunted house so that I can relax...</i>

314
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:49,710
<i>Compared to her in the lead role, 
my nerves aren't really anything significant.</i>

315
00:17:49,710 --> 00:17:53,170
<i>For her sake, too, I want to 
make sure the play goes well.</i>

316
00:17:53,170 --> 00:17:54,270
<i>But still...</i>

317
00:17:54,270 --> 00:17:56,140
<i>President being scared of the haunted house...</i>

318
00:17:56,140 --> 00:17:57,370
<i>is so cute.</i>

319
00:17:58,200 --> 00:18:00,110
What are you grinning about?

320
00:18:00,110 --> 00:18:04,080
Why can't you be proactive 
and walk ahead as my escort?

321
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:05,430
Oh, I'm sorry.

322
00:18:05,430 --> 00:18:06,700
Sheesh.

323
00:18:12,570 --> 00:18:14,930
S-S-S-Spider! Spider!

324
00:18:13,900 --> 00:18:15,710
Please calm down.

325
00:18:15,710 --> 00:18:17,200
<i>Ahhh, th-these...</i>

326
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:18,740
<i>These are her breasts pushing against me!</i>

327
00:18:21,370 --> 00:18:22,720
H-Huge spider!

328
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:24,610
A huge spider has my leg!

329
00:18:24,610 --> 00:18:26,040
It's fine!

330
00:18:31,160 --> 00:18:33,210
Please wait, President!

331
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:35,800
It's dangerous to run like that!

332
00:18:38,690 --> 00:18:39,920
Shirota-kun!

333
00:18:39,920 --> 00:18:41,730
M-My body won't move!

334
00:18:41,730 --> 00:18:43,710
Is it the curse?! Am I paralyzed?!

335
00:18:43,710 --> 00:18:44,990
Please calm down!

336
00:18:44,990 --> 00:18:47,550
You just got stuck in the spider web set!

337
00:18:47,550 --> 00:18:50,600
Maybe you crashed into it when you were 
running without looking ahead.

338
00:18:52,140 --> 00:18:55,100
Well, since I displayed this much shock,

339
00:18:55,100 --> 00:18:58,480
I'm sure the students from this class 
were quite happy as well.

340
00:18:58,480 --> 00:19:00,240
<i>She's still acting tough?!</i>

341
00:19:00,660 --> 00:19:03,320
Please wait. I'll untie you right away.

342
00:19:05,270 --> 00:19:07,100
You're really stuck, huh...

343
00:19:07,100 --> 00:19:09,320
Ahh! It grabbed my leg!

344
00:19:09,320 --> 00:19:10,790
Damn, that was close!

345
00:19:11,420 --> 00:19:13,580
<i>The next guests have caught up to us?!</i>

346
00:19:13,580 --> 00:19:17,010
<i>This is bad. If they were 
to see President in this state...</i>

347
00:19:17,970 --> 00:19:19,380
P-President?!

348
00:19:19,380 --> 00:19:22,200
Um, that's pretty avant-garde...

349
00:19:23,310 --> 00:19:26,180
<i>President's pure image will be destroyed.</i>

350
00:19:26,930 --> 00:19:28,090
<i>What do I do?!</i>

351
00:19:28,090 --> 00:19:29,600
<i>What should we do?!</i>

352
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:31,800
They've put quite some effort into it, huh?

353
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:33,780
Yeah, the atmosphere is pretty good, too.

354
00:19:35,530 --> 00:19:39,530
Oh foolish intruders unfazed by the curse...

355
00:19:40,050 --> 00:19:43,470
Shall I also turn you into spider people...?

356
00:19:44,740 --> 00:19:46,820
Is it me or did the quality just tank?

357
00:19:46,820 --> 00:19:47,980
What a joke.

358
00:19:48,420 --> 00:19:51,210
Couldn't you think of anything better?

359
00:19:51,700 --> 00:19:53,000
I'm sorry...

360
00:19:56,010 --> 00:19:59,460
I'm sorry. You went through 
so much for my sake...

361
00:19:59,950 --> 00:20:02,700
I don't how you misinterpreted the situation,

362
00:20:02,700 --> 00:20:05,240
but everything went according to my plan.

363
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:06,210
Huh?

364
00:20:06,210 --> 00:20:09,810
Didn't you realize that not only 
did you relax in the haunted house,

365
00:20:09,810 --> 00:20:12,560
you also got to act in front of other people?

366
00:20:12,940 --> 00:20:17,570
I got rid of your nerves, and by pretending 
to get into a sticky situation,

367
00:20:17,570 --> 00:20:21,440
I seamlessly enabled you to do a rehearsal.

368
00:20:22,170 --> 00:20:25,030
I-I see. Thank you very much.

369
00:20:25,460 --> 00:20:28,200
<i>It's impressive that she can 
come up with such an excuse.</i>

370
00:20:28,620 --> 00:20:29,720
<i></i>Waiting Room

371
00:20:33,860 --> 00:20:35,510
<i>There's some sort of commotion...</i>

372
00:20:39,300 --> 00:20:40,560
Did something happen?

373
00:20:41,060 --> 00:20:44,330
Well, it seems Ouji 
still hasn't come to school!

374
00:20:44,330 --> 00:20:45,130
What?

375
00:20:45,130 --> 00:20:46,560
Did he call in sick?

376
00:20:46,560 --> 00:20:49,680
No, but we can't reach him 
on his phone either...

377
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:52,820
Without Ouji, we won't 
be able to put on the play!

378
00:20:55,040 --> 00:20:56,800
Hey, sorry about that.

379
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:57,890
I'm late.

380
00:20:57,890 --> 00:20:58,820
Dude, Ouji!

381
00:20:58,820 --> 00:21:00,120
We worried abo—

382
00:21:00,120 --> 00:21:01,950
What?!!

383
00:21:01,950 --> 00:21:04,670
Yeah, well, I had a bit of a run-in...

384
00:21:04,670 --> 00:21:05,410
with a dump truck.

385
00:21:05,410 --> 00:21:06,740
A dump truck?!

386
00:21:06,740 --> 00:21:08,400
It's fine.

387
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:09,950
Not a proble— arghh.

388
00:21:09,950 --> 00:21:10,880
He's seriously hurt!

389
00:21:10,880 --> 00:21:11,710
Who's on first aid duty?!

390
00:21:11,250 --> 00:21:13,310
President, I'll put some on you right away,

391
00:21:11,710 --> 00:21:13,550
Take him to the nurse's office!

392
00:21:13,310 --> 00:21:15,790
You can make it so 
Ouji didn't have an accident.

393
00:21:13,550 --> 00:21:15,790
Stop! I'm fine!

394
00:21:16,280 --> 00:21:17,590
Let go of me!

395
00:21:17,590 --> 00:21:19,720
I can still do it!

396
00:21:19,720 --> 00:21:22,380
I am the Ouji—

397
00:21:22,380 --> 00:21:23,940
Let's find a replacement.

398
00:21:23,940 --> 00:21:24,970
A replacement?!

399
00:21:25,330 --> 00:21:27,160
<i>Why take such a risk?!</i>

400
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:30,390
<i>I thought she wanted to make 
100% sure this play goes well...</i>

401
00:21:30,830 --> 00:21:33,210
We have one hour until the start.

402
00:21:33,620 --> 00:21:36,890
It might be tight, but we 
should be ready on time.

403
00:21:38,060 --> 00:21:40,900
Okay, but who's supposed to be the Prince?

404
00:21:40,900 --> 00:21:43,360
We all have our own roles already...

405
00:21:43,360 --> 00:21:44,570
You're right.

406
00:21:44,570 --> 00:21:47,110
Why don't we do this, then?

407
00:21:47,500 --> 00:21:51,560
We pick a role where cutting it
won't affect the story much.

408
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:54,410
That actor will then step in for the Prince.

409
00:21:58,710 --> 00:22:01,170
That's you, Shirota-kun.

410
00:22:01,170 --> 00:22:05,420
<i>I-I'm supposed to replace Ouji?!</i>

